==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: one-woman
<hw>one-woman</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Designed for or restricted to a
single person; same as <altname>one-man</altname>, but used when the
person in question is female, or to avoid sexist language; <as>as, a
<ex>one-woman</ex> submarine; a <ex>one-woman</ex> show</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> one-man, one-person.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

